programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: It's all Because of the Lollipop
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds himself a treat of a large lollipop. After gorging on it, Joe places the hollowed lollipop around his neck and starts to toy with it. Not until he tries in vain to remove the lolly does he realize that he is stuck in it. As the lolly around Joe’s neck begins to melt, it becomes sticky and attracts many leaves to it. Joe looks just like a scary monster in that leafy lollipop! The other bug buddies are all frightened at the sight of Joe, mistaking him for the ruthless monster that has swallowed Joe alive. To revenge their good friend, the folks conceive a plan to capture “the monster”. Joe is cornered into a big ditch, where the lollipop around his neck is broken apart by McBroom’s dung ball. Not until then do the folks realize that the “monster” is none other than Joe Croaker! Just when the frog is about to fly off the handle, his buddies have already made themselves scarce.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is intrigued when he sees Niddy travels with her silk. The frog believes he might be able to do the same.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Joe's got a Fish Bone in His Throat
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is on the prowl for food and the fish obtained by Cosmo makes his mouth water. As is typical of Joe Croaker the greedy bully frog, he snatches the fish from Cosmo and quickly swallows it whole. But such voracity only results in the bones being stuck in Joe’s throat. Seeing Joe in great pain, Cosmo is in panic and at a loss what to do to help. At that moment, Bartle Bee happens to pass by and offers Joe his nectar to help ease the pain. But it fails to work. Then Bartle suggests two possible solutions he learnt from books, which are ramming down the bones with a bun and dissolving them with vinegar. Cosmo and Joe hurry to the Garbage can and score both a bun and a bottle of vinegar, but it turns out neither way helps remove the bones from Joe’s throat. In the end, proposed again by the resourceful Bartle Bee, they hang Joe Croaker upside down and succeed in swinging the bones out of Joe’s throat.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Fed up living in his shabby can house, Cosmo decides to find himself a sleek, cozy new place. First he is taken with the fancy-looking paper box with pretty patterns and good light, but Bartle Bee reminds him of its vulnerability to rain in wet seasons. So he keeps on searching his dream home. Then, a crystal clear glass jar commands Cosmo’s attention. Just when he is about to make it his new abode, the mole cricket’s warning against this heat-accumulating material discourages him from settling down there. So Cosmo has to look for other alternatives. Then he discovers a large magnet which he uses to attract pieces of parts together and make them into a solidly constructed iron house. After a long day’s rushing about, Cosmo retires to rest at his pleasant new home. But something bad happens. A coin is drawn to the magnet house and blocks the exit. Trapped inside his own house, Cosmo shouts for help, which invites Joe Croaker over. The frog agrees to help him out on the condition that Cosmo offers him both service and food. But instead of getting Cosmo out, Joe accidentally sets a large iron lid running, which crashes into the magnet house. Luckily enough, Cosmo is able to survive with the help of the mole cricket. In the end, Joe Croaker has to compensate Cosmo by offering him his service instead.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo has got a nice ice cream postage stamp, which is overheard by Joe Croaker. The thought of the tasty ice cream tempts the amphibian into a plot to steal the stamp from Cosmo. He tails Cosmo, and tries in vain to grab the stamp. Tired from the flight, Cosmo rests himself upon a branch, covering himself with the stamp. Seeing this as a good opportunity, Joe employs every possible method known to him to try to score the stamp. But none of them really works. Then the green vines hanging down the tree inspire him. He uses the vines to climb up and reaches out for the stamp. He then falls off onto the ground along with the stamp. Just when Joe assumes he has secured the ice cream stamp for good, a gust of wind blows it up to the tree again. Cosmo wakes up and joyfully takes the stamp back home.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Tiki chases their kite to Old Billy’s vegetable patch, and accidentally trample the vegetables. Although they try to correct the deed, but it just get worse. They try to avoid Old Billy in school and hesitate to apologize to him, for fear Old Billy will be angry. Briar tries to get Tiki and apologize to Old Billy. The old man tells them he’s going to the vegetable field to grow new vegetables. Briar and Tiki help him out. At last, they tell Old Billy the truth. The old man doesn’t get angry. Instead, he thinks they are responsible kids.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo doesn’t want to keep her old or broken toys, and asks her parents to buy her new ones. So she secretly throws away her old toys. When she visits Violet’s home, however, she finds out her friends treasure her toys very much, and remembers the good times she has spent with her toys. Then it rains. Luna-Loo quickly goes outside to find her toys with Violet but can’t find them. She’s feels regret. The next morning, she’s surprised to find out that all her toys are back. It turns out her mom picks up those toys, cleans and mends them. Luna-Loo realizes her mistake and thanks her mom. Violet and Vick come to Luna-Loo’s home and help her modify some old toys. Everyone is happy.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Summoning the Sun & The Frog Friends
programme.desc: Luna-Loo stays at Violet’s home for the night. They borrow a toy car from Vick powered by solar energy. However, the car runs out of power at night. They are disappointed to find out the sun has already set. They decide to summon the sun. First they to use some “magic spells”, then an ice cream to “entice” the sun to come out. They even mimic the sound of roosters to try to call for the sun. The sun never comes out. Instead, Violet’s parents are woken by the noise. Through a little experiment, they explain to the kids about solar rotation and the switch of night and day.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Bramble discover that Old Billy’s office smells bad. They decide to help him get rid of the awful smell. They try to collect some fresh clean air from a flower field with bottles, and bring the air to the office. However, it’s hard to tell whether the fragrance is really inside the bottles. So they decide to use balloons to collect the scent. However, a little hedgehog accidentally pops the balloons when he tries to help them. Old Billy sees them and tells them that the stinky smell will go away if they keep good ventilation in the office.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Briar has a toothache and Vick tells him there are bugs eating his teeth, making him anxious. To get the bugs out, they try many methods, such as gargling water, asking Hoo Hoo to peck the bugs out, and singing to lure the bugs out, all of which are proven to be useless. At last, they go to see Nurse Beakman, then they find out the cause of tooth decay, and learn how to protect their teeth.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Violet has a treasure chest, inside which Luna-Loo likes the moon stone the most. That day, Luna-Loo hides the treasure chest somewhere else without Violet’s permission, but what she doesn’t know is that Ms. Lady Jane witnesses the whole thing. The cubs are busy helping Violet look for the chest, while Luna-Loo is invited to Ms. Lady Jane’s office, where she hears Violet’s words about how she cherishes the chest. Luna-Loo realizes what she has done is not right. Ms. Lady Jane comes in. She asks Luna-Loo to return a screwdriver to Vick, and tells her that even though she likes the screwdriver, she can’t keep it because she’s not the owner. Luna-Loo puts the chest back and makes a confession to her friends.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: The Family Visit & You Get What You Put In
programme.desc: Little Briar misbehaves at kindergarten and refuses to apologize to the other kids. Ms. Olivia happens to go to the kids’ home for family visits. Briar is afraid that mom will learn about his behavior at kindergarten, so he tries various means to stop the family visit. Despite of this, Ms. Olivia still meets Briar’s mom. Seeing he could do nothing to stop the family visit, Briar tells the truth. Ms. Olivia tells Briar that he needs to confront his problems, and Briar learns a valuable lesson.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Tiki the Weatherman & Herby’s Helpful Apples
programme.desc: Old Billy forecasts the weather right, and Tiki asks Old Billy to teach him how to forecast a rainy day. Tiki makes notes and memorizes it. The other kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten plan to have a picnic, and Tiki tells them the weather will be sunny. However, just when the kids are going to have the picnic, it rains. Tiki goes to find Old Billy and asks him what’s wrong with the weather forecast. Old Billy explains that nature changes constantly and that only by studying hard could they make weather forecasts as accurate as possible.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Kitty the Tiger & The Magic Words
programme.desc: An uninvited guest, Kitty the tiger, sneaks into the drawing class, and shocks the whole class. But later this adorable tiger wins everybody’s heart. They like her, and volunteer to look after her. Kitty makes much trouble. However to make her happy, Prince Tiki lets her have his favorite bag. During naptime, kitty misses her mom so much that she can’t stop crying. Then the kids sing for her to help her sleep. It’s time to say goodbye. Everybody feels sad to part with her. Ms. Olivia promises that Kitty will attend the kindergarten when she grows up, making them happy again.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Fierce begs Guardian to teach him martial arts, and Guardian lies to him that the secret of success is smile. Fierce takes his words seriously and keeps smiling all day, which scares his companions away. The martial arts competition kicks off on the next day. Fierce jumps onto the arena first and Poppy follows to take up the challenge. Just as the master predicted, Poppy knocks out Fierce with the slightest effort.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Guardian keeps bragging about his glorious past and Fierce gets tired of his jawing away. Fierce plucks some wild fruits from a tree to eat, which makes him suffer from diarrhea. They take a short break and continue the journey. Several hours later, Fierce finds that he has passed the same fruit tree he met just now for three times and they are walking around in a circle. But Guardian doesn’t listen to him and moves on.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Fierce and Guardian thank Cloud Hand for his delicious food and prepare to start off. Cloud Hand tells them they can stay overnight at his house because there are many bumpy roads nearby and they may get lost easily. Guardian refuses his invitation politely and draws Fierce away. But soon after, they cannot find their way and come back again. Cloud Hand makes up a guest room for them and says he’ll show them the way out of the forest the next morning.

programme.title: Origins Of The Twelve
programme.desc: Cloud Hand is hung upside down on a tree with his feet tied. The branch breaks off and he drops onto the ground. Guardian says Cloud Hand must have been sleepwalking at night and tied himself to the tree. Cloud Hand falls for what he says and doesn’t feel angry at all. Guardian says the pig must have pretended to be so nice and they need to test his character. They throw a coin, an ingot of silver, and an ingot of gold onto the ground on purpose, only to find that Cloud Hand is not interested in them at all and just cares about his food materials. They put off their doubts completely and begin to enjoy the dishes Cloud Hand cooks.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: The cubs break the trophy they won at the sports meeting. Fear of being criticized by Ms. Oliva, they make up a story that a blue bird attacks Briar and accidentally breaks the trophy. Ms. Olivia sees through their lie and gives them a lesson on honesty. The cubs confess their fault, and fix the trophy together.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Bramble decides to keep the caterpillar he finds on his head, and see how it grows up and becomes a butterfly. As time goes by, the caterpillar becomes a pupa, and soon it will turn into a butterfly. But in the process of metamorphosis, Bramble worries that it might get stuck, and tries to help. Ms. Olivia stops him and tells him that it needs to do it itself to get enough strength to fly. Just as they expected, the butterfly finally comes out, dries its wings, and flies.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: The kids at Pine Tree Kindergarten are discussing what they want to be when they grow up. Vick says he wants to be an inventor and boasts that it’s easy to invent. To prove his point, he wants to invent something to dig holes as well as something for him to fly. However, both inventions meet with failure. Just when he is discouraged, he sees little Briar and Tiki playing paper planes. They are having a little contest. Then Vick gets an idea when he sees Bramble’s balloon. He attaches the balloon to the paper plane, and invents a “balloon plane” which could fly the most distance.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: The cubs have got a new classmate – Ernie Jo, whose ears look different. A rumor starts that Ernie Jo’s big ears are infectious. Everybody tries to avoid him until Babu touches one of his ear by accident and he’s totally fine. The rumor is cleared and the cubs accept him. They invite Ernie Jo to play hide and seek. With the help of his big ears, Ernie Jo leads the cubs to find Little Vick who has fallen asleep and snores during the game. Now everybody wishes to have big ears like Ernie Jo’s do.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Rainy Day Fun & The More, The Better?
programme.desc: Violet hates rainy days. She doesn’t get why the others are having fun as usual. She tries to practice her flute, but rain drops cause her flute to get out of tune. Violet gets quite embarrassed and bursts into tears. To comfort her, everybody else gets busy doing funny tricks. Violet stops crying, asks why they enjoy the rain, and finds her own fun on rainy days.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: It's all Because of the Lollipop
programme.desc: Joe Croaker finds himself a treat of a large lollipop. After gorging on it, Joe places the hollowed lollipop around his neck and starts to toy with it. Not until he tries in vain to remove the lolly does he realize that he is stuck in it. As the lolly around Joe’s neck begins to melt, it becomes sticky and attracts many leaves to it. Joe looks just like a scary monster in that leafy lollipop! The other bug buddies are all frightened at the sight of Joe, mistaking him for the ruthless monster that has swallowed Joe alive. To revenge their good friend, the folks conceive a plan to capture “the monster”. Joe is cornered into a big ditch, where the lollipop around his neck is broken apart by McBroom’s dung ball. Not until then do the folks realize that the “monster” is none other than Joe Croaker! Just when the frog is about to fly off the handle, his buddies have already made themselves scarce.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is intrigued when he sees Niddy travels with her silk. The frog believes he might be able to do the same.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.sub-title: Joe's got a Fish Bone in His Throat
programme.desc: Joe Croaker is on the prowl for food and the fish obtained by Cosmo makes his mouth water. As is typical of Joe Croaker the greedy bully frog, he snatches the fish from Cosmo and quickly swallows it whole. But such voracity only results in the bones being stuck in Joe’s throat. Seeing Joe in great pain, Cosmo is in panic and at a loss what to do to help. At that moment, Bartle Bee happens to pass by and offers Joe his nectar to help ease the pain. But it fails to work. Then Bartle suggests two possible solutions he learnt from books, which are ramming down the bones with a bun and dissolving them with vinegar. Cosmo and Joe hurry to the Garbage can and score both a bun and a bottle of vinegar, but it turns out neither way helps remove the bones from Joe’s throat. In the end, proposed again by the resourceful Bartle Bee, they hang Joe Croaker upside down and succeed in swinging the bones out of Joe’s throat.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Fed up living in his shabby can house, Cosmo decides to find himself a sleek, cozy new place. First he is taken with the fancy-looking paper box with pretty patterns and good light, but Bartle Bee reminds him of its vulnerability to rain in wet seasons. So he keeps on searching his dream home. Then, a crystal clear glass jar commands Cosmo’s attention. Just when he is about to make it his new abode, the mole cricket’s warning against this heat-accumulating material discourages him from settling down there. So Cosmo has to look for other alternatives. Then he discovers a large magnet which he uses to attract pieces of parts together and make them into a solidly constructed iron house. After a long day’s rushing about, Cosmo retires to rest at his pleasant new home. But something bad happens. A coin is drawn to the magnet house and blocks the exit. Trapped inside his own house, Cosmo shouts for help, which invites Joe Croaker over. The frog agrees to help him out on the condition that Cosmo offers him both service and food. But instead of getting Cosmo out, Joe accidentally sets a large iron lid running, which crashes into the magnet house. Luckily enough, Cosmo is able to survive with the help of the mole cricket. In the end, Joe Croaker has to compensate Cosmo by offering him his service instead.

programme.title: Pondemonium
programme.desc: Cosmo has got a nice ice cream postage stamp, which is overheard by Joe Croaker. The thought of the tasty ice cream tempts the amphibian into a plot to steal the stamp from Cosmo. He tails Cosmo, and tries in vain to grab the stamp. Tired from the flight, Cosmo rests himself upon a branch, covering himself with the stamp. Seeing this as a good opportunity, Joe employs every possible method known to him to try to score the stamp. But none of them really works. Then the green vines hanging down the tree inspire him. He uses the vines to climb up and reaches out for the stamp. He then falls off onto the ground along with the stamp. Just when Joe assumes he has secured the ice cream stamp for good, a gust of wind blows it up to the tree again. Cosmo wakes up and joyfully takes the stamp back home.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Briar and Tiki chases their kite to Old Billy’s vegetable patch, and accidentally trample the vegetables. Although they try to correct the deed, but it just get worse. They try to avoid Old Billy in school and hesitate to apologize to him, for fear Old Billy will be angry. Briar tries to get Tiki and apologize to Old Billy. The old man tells them he’s going to the vegetable field to grow new vegetables. Briar and Tiki help him out. At last, they tell Old Billy the truth. The old man doesn’t get angry. Instead, he thinks they are responsible kids.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.desc: Luna-Loo doesn’t want to keep her old or broken toys, and asks her parents to buy her new ones. So she secretly throws away her old toys. When she visits Violet’s home, however, she finds out her friends treasure her toys very much, and remembers the good times she has spent with her toys. Then it rains. Luna-Loo quickly goes outside to find her toys with Violet but can’t find them. She’s feels regret. The next morning, she’s surprised to find out that all her toys are back. It turns out her mom picks up those toys, cleans and mends them. Luna-Loo realizes her mistake and thanks her mom. Violet and Vick come to Luna-Loo’s home and help her modify some old toys. Everyone is happy.

programme.title: Masters of the Zodiac
programme.sub-title: Summoning the Sun & The Frog Friends
programme.desc: Luna-Loo stays at Violet’s home for the night. They borrow a toy car from Vick powered by solar energy. However, the car runs out of power at night. They are disappointed to find out the sun has already set. They decide to summon the sun. First they to use some “magic spells”, then an ice cream to “entice” the sun to come out. They even mimic the sound of roosters to try to call for the sun. The sun never comes out. Instead, Violet’s parents are woken by the noise. Through a little experiment, they explain to the kids about solar rotation and the switch of night and day.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Ray uncovers the secrets of America’s greatest racing sport in the foothills of North Carolina. When moonshiners were looking to outrun police officers, they would custom fit engines to race the back woods tracks. That sport eventually evolved into NASCAR and Ray talks to the early adopters of this national pastime.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Grammy-winning musician Marty Robbins lived a double life, flawlessly crossing between the glitz of the Grand Ole Opry and track at Talladega. One of few musicians to ever achieve success in both genres, Ray is determined to return Marty’s iconic 777 car to the race track travel back to the 60’s and 70’s.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Legendary drag racer Don “The Snake” Prudhomme proves he is no stranger to the thrill of racing rivalry. Prudhomme’s career and subsequent competition with driver Tom “The Mongoose” McEwan earned the pair an unforgettable imprint on American pop culture. Legions of kids in the 60’s and 70’s flocked to the shelves for Snake and Mongoose Matchbox cars which helped make drag racing an undisputable American pastime. Famed director Ron Howard makes an appearance to discuss the incredible stories hidden within the world of Formula 1 Racing, the topic of his latest, epic feature ‘Rush”.

programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: Ray finds Buried Treasures in the form of two race cars that had been left almost completely untouched since the last time they were on a race track. programme.title: AmeriCarna
programme.desc: A journey to Indianapolis unveils the winning car of the 1955 Indy 500 sits on the roof of an auto mechanic shop. programme.title: AmeriCarna

programme.desc: Everyone has their own dreams. That of Smurfette is to meet the legendary Don Smurfo, the dashing, witty, swashbuckling hero of many an engrossing tale. The Smurfs shrug at this infatuation. But when a real-life Don Smurfo appears in the village and Smurfette snubs them all in favor of the bragging stranger, they take the matter a little more seriously.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Balthazar brings Denisa to Gargamel to baby-sit. But Gargamel loses Denisa in the wood and she and Sassette meet and become friends. Sassette and Denisa work together to free the Smurfs from Gargamel's stewpot, and prove you don't have to be big to be brave.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs find a baby dragon that has gotten lost in the forest. They take it back to the village and look after it. But wicked Gargamel manages to capture the poor creature and plans to use it to destroy the Smurf village. Luckily Papa Smurf has more than one trick up his sleeve.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Once in a blue moon, as the legend goes, a baby Smurf is delivered to the Smurfs and everyone in the village becomes attached to the new arrival. But a mistake has been made and the stork returns to take the baby back. Grouchy and Smurfette have become so attached to the baby that the baby is returned.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Oh dear! Sassette has lost a tooth. Papa Smurf explains that if she puts her tooth under her pillow, the Mouse Fairy will bring her a present in the morning. But the next morning there is no present under the pillow. The Mouse Fairy has not been. She has been captured in one of Gargamel’s Smurf traps. And now the evil wizard is concocting a dreadful plan.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Clumsy, wanting to be popular, steals one of Gargamel's magic spells but it backfires and turns him into a dragon. It takes all of the little blue people and Papa Smurf to sneak back to the wizard's castle to find the antidote that turns Clumsy back to his normal smurfy self.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: What a strange stone Clumsy has unearthed! In it, he can see events that are going to happen... Yet knowing part of the future sometimes brings bad luck!

programme.title: The Kaplowey Scroll
programme.desc: There is a terrifying magic word. When you direct the word at something or someone, you make it vanish into nothingness! Can the Smurfs undo its evil power before Gargamel gets hold of it?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's worries make him break into a rash of worrywarts. The only way to relieve him of his bout of indecision-inducing disease is to have him rub the horn of a Wartmonger, a sloppy, slimy, stupid and brutal enemy of the Pussywillow Pixies...

programme.title: Smurfette's Gift
programme.desc: Every year, Smurfette snoops around to discover what her birthday presents will be before she receives them. But this year, Sassette has created the Keep-Smurfette's-Presents-a-Surprise-Committee. Nat has discovered a cave where they might be able to hide all the gifts prepared by the Smurfs. But what this cave also hides is a greedy imp who is not only interested in keeping Smurfette's gifts...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Each morning, dew is deposited by water sprites on forest leaves. Wait till you see what happens when Scaredy Smurf gets hold of the dew-making magic wand...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In old China, there is a fortune to be found in Greedy's Smurf cookies and Brainy is the writer. But the opportunity for mischief is too good to miss for Jokey Smurf.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: His wicked cousin, Malcolm the Mean, who plans to kill him and mount him in his trophy room, has turned King Gerard into a black stag. The little Smurfs help their friend. When King Gerard is transformed back into his human form, Malcolm becomes imprisoned in the body of the stag.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When Brainy loses his glasses, he drops things, runs into objects, and becomes just as helpless as Clumsy, who now has to read to Brainy and help him get around. This experience makes Brainy feel guilty for the way he always made fun of Clumsy. He treats him with more respect once he receives a new pair of glasses.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Smurf Friendship Day is that time in the year when, more than ever, the Smurfs show friendliness to one another. But won't Chlorhydris destroy those good feelings? And how can the Smurfs find a way to exchange Cupid's arrows for something nicer?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Baby Smurf has lost all interest in toys. Even Jokey's surprises fail to amuse the tiny tyke. Grandpa Smurf suggests they go and pay a visit to the Toymaker, the one who makes toys for children all over the world. Or rather used to make: the Toymaker is tired of the lack of appreciation his toys receive from those who receive them.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: What is in the box that's been found by Jokey Smurf? A cloak belonging to Wizlow the Magician gnome. And what sort of cloak? Jokey learns that it's a cloak of invisibility. Whoever wears it has a great opportunity of playing practical jokes... And guess what havoc an invisible Jokey is able to wreak on the Village. Yet if Wizlow parted with the cloak, there must be a reason...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It's not every day you meet a talking flower. Especially not a character like Petaluma, a somewhat haughty bulb flower who Smurfette meets in the forest. Of course the delighted Smurfette takes Petaluma to the Village of the Smurfs... and starts a process that is going to endanger all of the Smurfs. Flowers, it seems, ought to be seen and not heard.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Directing the Smurfs to finish repairing the dam, Papa Smurf takes off on a herb-hunting expedition. While he is gone, Brainy causes havoc when he declares himself King and Papa Smurf returns just in time to save the dam from bursting.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brenda, the little witch, feels rejected: no-one is taking her to this year's Broomstick Ball. Oh, if she could find some nice-looking boy... Then she meets Scruple, apprentice of the evil wizard Gargamel. He's so handsome, and available too! What she does not know is that Scruple's only interest is her magic wand. What the Smurfs know is that they're going to save the day.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The evil Maestro's magical paints have the power to transport his models onto canvas – forever! Papa Smurf directs Painter to switch his paints and before long, Maestro is enshrined in a picture next to his dream girl, Smurfette.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: Smurf A Mile In My Shoes
programme.desc: The Smurfs band together to retrieve a sea-shell they need to release a hermit imp from the Sea Witch, as she cursed him with ugliness and a language very few understand. The Smurfs return with the sea-shell in time to break the curse and return the hermit to the handsome imp he once was.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs discover a fountain of youth that is guarded by a wicked troll, who steals Papa Smurf's magic book. They convince Gargamel to help them and the greedy villain runs to get the water, but manages to fall in with the troll. As the two chase each other all over the countryside, the Smurfs are able to retrieve Papa Smurf's book.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa instructs adult Smurfs (Nat, Snappy and Slouchy) to deliver an hourglass to Father Time. While there, the three step inside a clock which is running backwards and they go back in time. Father Time says there is no way to make them older. All must accept them as Smurflings and learn that they have a lot to offer.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Determined to fly over Smurf village to catch a Smurf to take to the Wizard's Convention, Gargamel invokes his Book of Spells to help him. A series of funny flying machine mishaps occur and Gargamel is once more the laughing stock of the Wizard's Convention.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: The Smurf Who Would Be King
programme.desc: Dreamy yearns to be King after reading a story about them. He falls through a whirlpool while on his ship and finds himself in the land of pokies who think Dreamy is their long-lost King. When he confronts the pokies' enemies, the Norfnags, he finds they aren't fearful at all. Dreamy bumps his head and wakes up to discover it was just a dream, yet finds a jewel in his cap, just like the ones the pokies mine for a living.

programme.title: Skyscraper Smurfs
programme.desc: Sure, a village of mushroom-shaped houses is nice and jolly... But not very modern, in Architect Smurf's view. What the Smurfs need is smurfdominium, a new, daring concept that will change the art of living forever...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs discover a fountain of youth that is guarded by a wicked troll, who steals Papa Smurf's magic book. They convince Gargamel to help them and the greedy villain runs to get the water, but manages to fall in with the troll. As the two chase each other all over the countryside, the Smurfs are able to retrieve Papa Smurf's book.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Gargamel feels that creating the Smurfette was the worst mistake of his life. Now, if he could change her back to her original nasty self, he would get all the Smurfs in one fell swoop... Will Smurfette revert to her evil ways?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When the Smurfs reach Ancient China, they learn that the child Emperor is in danger of being deposed, and by whom? By the evil Garg-Fu-Yun, who wants to rule in the child's stead!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The evil wizard Gargamel has got hold of magical ectoplasmic crystal eggs that will enable him to change bodies with Papa Smurf. What better plan could there be? Disguised as Papa Smurf, he's going to lead all the Smurfs to his cauldron! But as fate would have it, Gargamel is changed into Puppy, the Smurf doggie...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grouchy, the Smurf who hates everything, doubly hates his own birthday party and goes to hide in Shadow Swamp... He is going to meet strange beings and stranger adventures while the other Smurfs search for him...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Posing for a sculpture, especially a huge composition like that of Painter Smurf, is very tiring work, and you can't help moving a little. Now Papa Smurf finds a way to keep the posers perfectly still. There are drawbacks though, as the Smurfs will soon realise...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grandpa has never acted his age, but here he is, younger than ever, after having been touched by the water of the Fountain of Youth. Sassette will have to watch the 1000-year-old kid...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.sub-title: The Smurfs And The Money Tree
programme.desc: The wicked wizard Gargamel has come up with yet another diabolical plan with the help of his mother, who isn't much nicer than him. He wants to tempt the Smurfs with money of which they have no notion. Will Greedy take the bait?

programme.title: The Colour Smurf
programme.desc: Spectra is the Colour Fairy, the one whose wheel of colours make all the blues, reds, yellows and greens of the world. She is a friend of Painter Smurf, so when he takes the Smurflings to her home in her absence, the Smurflings fool around with the Colour Wheel... and all the colours disappear from the Earth. What's worse, without colours the Colour Fairy cannot live...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Greedy is a connoisseur of fine food. But in Ancient Rome he discovers a delicious new dish and decides he wants to learn the recipe. But first, Greedy will have to win a contest.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In his search for something new, Vanity dons a Gargamel-made magic hat that transforms his face into a mess. Through trickery, Papa Smurf gets the antidote from the wicked wizard and once more, Vanity is beautiful.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Selwyn and Tallulah are two powerful married wizards. The trouble is, they fight all the time. But the energy from their arguments is brewing up a dreadful storm and Papa has to get them to make up before the storm starts to rage.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It must be something she ate. The chicken that laid the painted eggs now lays plain white eggs. The scene is Old Russia, and the Tsar is going to be mad if the Smurfs don't find a solution.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: In another Smurf theatrical super-production based – very loosely – on Alexandre Dumas' characters, a masterpiece of the stage is created, with a few lines from Romeo and Juliet thrown in.

programme.title: Reckless Smurfs
programme.desc: This time, Gargamel's plan cannot fail. Undeterred by Azrael's derisive cackling, the evil wizard perfects a magic substance called Daredevil Dust, which is going to change all the Smurfs into rash, incautious swashbucklers. Will Papa Smurf fall into Gargamel's trap? Will their enemy catch all the Smurfs? Will this story have a happy ending?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brenda, the little witch, feels rejected: no-one is taking her to this year's Broomstick Ball. Oh, if she could find some nice-looking boy... Then she meets Scruple, apprentice of the evil wizard Gargamel. He's so handsome, and available too! What she does not know is that Scruple's only interest is her magic wand. What the Smurfs know is that they're going to save the day.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: When a drop of Papa Smurf's new potion spills on the Smurflings' adventure book, the fictional hero springs to life. The dashing Don Smurfo, willing to rid the Smurf of the evil Gargamel, gallantly captures him...

programme.title: Gargamel's Mis-Fortune
programme.desc: Gargamel, the evil but incompetent wizard, tries to trick Esmeralda, the gypsy, into giving him a formula to catch the Smurfs. Of course the gypsy proves to be much smarter than Gargamel, and the Smurfs even more so.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It's not every day you meet a talking flower. Especially not a character like Petaluma, a somewhat haughty bulb flower who Smurfette meets in the forest. Of course the delighted Smurfette takes Petaluma to the Village of the Smurfs... and starts a process that is going to endanger all of the Smurfs. Flowers, it seems, ought to be seen and not heard.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Get up early in the morning, before any other Smurf is out of bed, to prepare a scrumptious Smurfberry muffin. Spend all morning on preparing Smurf delicacies for lunch. Than all afternoon to have dinner ready – and delicious – on time. And do you get so much as a thank you form the Smurfs? So Greedy Smurf quits. The Village is in trouble... And soon, so is Greedy.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Grandpa's ancient enemy, the evil warlock Nemesis, comes in search of Grandpa and the Smurfs' Long Life Stone. Will Grandpa be able to save the stone and himself from the powerful enchanter?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs come to the rescue of two children and their grandfather when a mysterious stranger appears and causes their sleigh to crash. Knocking on Gargamel's door for help puts them and the Smurfs in danger...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Each morning, dew is deposited by water sprites on forest leaves. Wait till you see what happens when Scaredy Smurf gets hold of the dew-making magic wand...

programme.title: Heavenly Smurfs
programme.desc: Once again, Gargamel's infallible plan to catch the Smurfs has been foiled. But the Smurfs play a trick on him: disguised as tiny blue angels, they will teach him to mend his ways...

programme.title: Poet The Know-It-All
programme.desc: Solomon the Soothsayer owns an amulet that enables its wearer to peer into the future. He gives it willingly (too willingly, perhaps) to Poet Smurf, who will be able from now on to tell of what's coming next...

programme.title: Brainy Smurf, Friend To All Animals
programme.desc: Brainy dons his safari hat and roams the forest to do good deeds for animals. He mostly gives advice to the creatures but balks when he can really save the life of a wildcat being hunted by Gargamel. Nat gives Brainy the courage to free the cat from Gargamel's trap.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The wise and prudent Papa Smurf, without whom the little blue people are helpless, is bitten by the Slumber bug in Ancient Japan. He falls asleep and, to wake him up, the Smurfs go on a journey...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A fierce wind carries the Smurfs' windmill away, with several Smurfs inside. Is Lazy Smurf really at fault or is an injustice being committed? Are the captive Smurfs going to be saved from the volcano's crater? Is Brainy going to smurf up his mouth for a moment?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It must be a coincidence: just as an elephant crosses the forest and meets baby Smurf, the Smurfs decide to create a big Smurf Circus. They are going to meet the infernal sorcerer Balthazar and Baby Smurf will have a lot of fun...

programme.title: Snappy's Way
programme.desc: Did you know that if you catch a troll, he may grant you one wish? It just happens that Aloysius the Troll gets caught in one of Gargamel's Smurf traps. Snappy Smurf sets him free and as a reward, gets to make all other Smurfs obey his every whim. Now this brings a lot of trouble to the Smurfs, as Smurflings, sometimes, ask for things that are not good for them... or anybody else.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A wicked sorceress casts a spell on the Smurfs, forcing them to love themselves and not each other. Vanity, who's always like that, was away at the time, but notices the change when he returns. He breaks the spell by getting all the Smurfs to eat humble pie baked by a wizard.

programme.title: Foul Weather Smurf
programme.desc: Handy invents a weather machine that will allow the Smurfs to control their environment at will. Unfortunately, they cannot agree on whether it should rain or be sunny so the machine overloads and explodes.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: This is the day of the annual boat race and all the Smurfs have designed their own craft, each with their own personality. But Gargamel can predict to the very minute when the boats are going to arrive at this bend of the river, and he has prepared a jolting surprise...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The starving Smurfs discover a cave that has a stash of frozen food inside guarded by an equally frozen troll who was imprisoned because of his greed by a magic diamond. As the Smurfs defrost the cave, Gargamel steals the food, but the magic diamond transforms him into an icy mass and the freed troll happily helps the Smurfs carry the food back to their village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha the witch promises Gargamel a magical whistle if he will introduce her to the warlock of her dreams. But they are both deceived by each other's trickery: Gargamel dresses up as the warlock, and Hogatha's magical whistle is only a birdcall.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The village of the Smurfs used to live without a clock. But now suddenly time becomes a precious commodity and Brainy Smurf designs a schedule to take advantage of the new Village clock... Can the Smurfs survive the attacks of time?

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Never eat candy offered by a stranger. Even if the candy is in the shape of a house, deep in the Black Forest. The Smurfs can't resist eating the candy house and trouble begins straight away.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: The Smurfs find a baby dragon that has gotten lost in the forest. They take it back to the village and look after it. But wicked Gargamel manages to capture the poor creature and plans to use it to destroy the Smurf village. Luckily Papa Smurf has more than one trick up his sleeve.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Every time Lazy falls asleep, he is caught in the same recurrent nightmare: he is in the power of Morphio, an evil sorcerer who wants to capture as many sleeping souls as possible. One after another, all the Smurfs are going to fall in Morphio's clutches. All of them? Well, maybe not, if Papa Smurf can help it. And Papa Smurf goes to the Sandman for help...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Hogatha disguises herself as the Golden Smurf Award to catch the Smurfs in order to use them as the main ingredient in her beauty cream. Vanity convinces her to try his recipe and before long, the wicked sorceress is covered with mud and sent careening over the hills into Gargamel's house.

programme.title: Secret Of The Village Well
programme.desc: Why is Clumsy Smurf waiting day and night near the Village well? What is the wish that he wants to be kept secret? How is Gargamel going to be mixed up in this mysterious affair? Is Gargamel going to catch the Smurfs at last?

programme.title: Essence Of Brainy
programme.desc: Brainy Smurf is not the same anymore. He is polite, considerate, modest and calls every other Smurf Sir or Madame. All the Smurfs are worried that Brainy has lost all that makes his personality. They ought to be worried, for Brainy has been the victim of a system called an Essence Remover that Scruple, Gargamel's apprentice, uses... But Brainy's essence is coming back!

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Brainy feels up to the occasion when he starts the recipe for cookies. He is sure to win the contest: he borrowed a recipe from Papa Smurf's Book of Magic. But a big surprise, and some nasty happenings, await poor Brainy... and the whole Village.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: Papa Smurf's worries make him break into a rash of worrywarts. The only way to relieve him of his bout of indecision-inducing disease is to have him rub the horn of a Wartmonger, a sloppy, slimy, stupid and brutal enemy of the Pussywillow Pixies...

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: A strange little imp who is a master at games challenges the Smurfs to a contest. He turns the Smurflings into rigid game pieces and forces Grouchy, who never wins at games, into playing for the Smurflings' lives. Grouchy gains confidence, makes the right move, and frees the Smurfs.

programme.title: The Smurfs
programme.desc: It must be something she ate. The chicken that laid the painted eggs now lays plain white eggs. The scene is Old Russia, and the Tsar is going to be mad if the Smurfs don't find a solution.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos no quieren ser bucaneros que roban oro de los galeones que pasan cerca de ellos. Sin embargo, caen bajo el hechizo de un amuleto magico y se convierten en la tripulacion del loro Picoazul.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando se produce una emergencia, todos los Pitufos de la aldea dejan lo que tienen entre manos y corren a oir las noticias. Pero que Pitufo Vanidoso convoque una asamblea para que los Pitufos puedan admirar su nuevo gorro es pasarse de la raya. Le echan de la aldea y Pitufo Vanidoso tiene la mala suerte de encontrarse con Lofty, el elfo, que le recomienda darse un horrible bano de fango...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Habia Una Vez Una Luna Azul
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban cogiendole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve a por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que la acaban devolviendoles el bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un extrano diablillo, que es todo un maestro de los juegos, desafia a los Pitufos en una competicion. Transforma a los Pitufitos en rigidas piezas de ajedrez y obliga a Pitufo Grunon, que nunca gana a ningun juego, a jugar para salvar las vidas de los Pitufitos. Pitufo Grunon va sintiendose mas seguro, realiza el movimiento correcto y consigue liberar a los Pitufos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo se siente preparado para la ocasion cuando empieza a preparar una receta de galletas. Esta convencido de que va a ganar el concurso, ya que ha tomado prestada una receta del libro de magia de Papa Pitufo. Sin embargo, una gran sorpresa y algunas situaciones desagradables aguardan al pobre Pitufo Filosofo y a toda la aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo no parece el mismo. Es educado, considerado, modesto y trata con cortesia a los demas Pitufos. A todos los Pitufos les preocupa que Pitufo Filosofo haya perdido todos los rasgos que conforman su personalidad. Y hacen bien en estar preocupados, ya que Filosofo ha sido victima de un artefacto denominado removedor de esencias que Escrupuloso, el aprendiz de Gargamel, esta utilizando... ¡Pero conseguiran recuperar la esencia de Filosofo!

programme.title: Don Pituzorro
programme.desc: Todo el mundo tiene sus propios suenos. El de Pitufina es conocer al legendario Don Pituzorro, el gallardo, ingenioso e intrepido heroe de numerosas y cautivadoras aventuras. Los Pitufos no toman en serio ese encaprichamiento. Sin embargo, cuando un Don Pituzorro real aparece en la aldea y Pitufina les ignora en favor del jactancioso extrano, se toman el asunto algo mas en serio.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Baltasar lleva a Denisa con Gargamel para que este haga de canguro. Sin embargo, Gargamel pierde a Denisa en el bosque y esta se encuentra con Sasita y se hace amiga de ella. Sasita y Denisa colaboran para sacar a los Pitufos del caldero de Gargamel y demostrar que la valentia no es cuestion de tamano.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo se encuentra indefenso cuando se le acaban las bayas magicas que utiliza para sus pociones. Afortunadamente, los pequenos Pitufos encuentran un bebe de dragon en el bosque y con su ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: Habia Una Vez Una Luna Azul
programme.desc: Una noche de Luna Azulada, tal y como la leyenda decia, un bebe pitufo aparece en el pueblo, y todos acaban cogiendole carino. Pero todo ha sido un malentendido y la ciguena vuelve a por el bebe. Pintor y Grunon se han encarinado tanto con el bebe que la acaban devolviendoles el bebe.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Madre mia! A Sasita se le ha caido un diente. Papa Pitufo le explica que, si coloca el diente bajo la almohada, encontrara un obsequio del hada de los dientes al dia siguiente. Sin embargo, a la manana siguiente no hay ningun regalo debajo de la almohada. El hada de los dientes no ha acudido. Resulta que esta atrapada en una de las trampas de Gargamel. Y ahora, el malvado mago esta tramando un terrible plan.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Tontin, al querer ser el mas popular, roba uno de los hechizos de Gargamel, pero no lo usa bien y acaba convirtiendose en un dragon. Ahora tendran que juntarse todos los Pitufos junto con Papa Pitufo para colarse en el castillo de Gargamel y encontrar el antidoto que hara que Pitufo Tontin vuelva a su forma normal.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¡Pitufo Torpe ha desenterrado una extrana piedra! En ella, puede ver los eventos que van a suceder... ¡No obstante, conocer parte del futuro a veces trae mala suerte!

programme.title: La Formula Aniquiladora
programme.desc: Existe una palabra magica aterradora. Cuando pronuncias esa palabra hacia algo o alguien, ¡haces que se desvanezca en la nada! ¿Podran los Pitufos anular su malvado poder antes de que Gargamel se apropie de ella?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las preocupaciones de Papa Pitufo hacen que le salgan verrugas. La unica forma de librarle de esta enfermedad causada por la indecision es que frote el cuerno de uno de los Verrugosos, los desalinados, viscosos, estupidos y brutales enemigos de las haditas del Bosque de los Sauces...

programme.title: El Regalo De Pitufina
programme.desc: Todos los anos, Pitufina se dedica a rebuscar para descubrir cuales seran sus regalos de cumpleanos antes de que se los entreguen. Sin embargo, este ano Sasita ha creado un comite para mantener en secreto los regalos de Pitufina. Pitufo Natural ha descubierto una cueva en la que podrian esconder todos los regalos preparados por los Pitufos. Sin embargo, en esa cueva tambien se esconde un codicioso diablillo que no solo esta interesado en los regalos de Pitufina...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En la antigua China, la fortuna se esconde en las galletas del Pitufo Goloso, y Pitufo Filosofo es el escritor. Es una oportunidad demasiado buena para hacer travesuras como para que Pitufo Bromista la desperdicie.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado primo del Rey, Malcolm, lo ha convertido en un ciervo negro para poder acabar con el y ponerle en su sala de trofeos. Los Pitufos iran a ayudar a su amigo y, tras devolver al Rey a su verdadera forma, Malcom acabara preso dentro del cuerpo del ciervo negro.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando el Pitufo Filosofo pierde sus gafas deja caer las cosas, tropieza con los objetos, y se convierte en tan patoso como el Pitufo Tontin, que ahora tiene que leer a Filosofo y ayudarle a manejarse. Esta experiencia hace que Filosofo se sienta culpable por la forma en la que siempre se ha burlado de Tontin. Una vez que recibe un nuevo par de gafas, le trata con mas respeto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El Pitufidia de la Amistad es el momento del ano en el que, mas que nunca, los Pitufos demuestran su amabilidad con los demas. ¿Conseguira Clorhidris destruir esos buenos sentimientos? ¿Y como pueden los Pitufos encontrar una forma de cambiar las flechas de Cupido por algo mas agradable?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Bebe Pitufo ha perdido el interes por los juguetes. Ni siquiera las sorpresas de Pitufo Bromista consiguen entretener al pequeno. Abuelo Pitufo propone hacer una visita al Juguetero, el encargado de fabricar juguetes para los ninos de todo el mundo. O mas bien, el que los fabricaba: el Juguetero esta cansado del poco aprecio que demuestran por sus juguetes aquellos que los reciben.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: ¿Que contiene la caja que ha encontrado Pitufo Bromista? Una capa que pertenecio a Wislow, el gnomo mago. ¿Y de que tipo de capa se trata? Pitufo Bromista descubre que es una capa de invisibilidad. Cualquiera que la lleve puesta tendra una oportunidad fantastica para hacer bromas... e imagina el caos que puede crear Pitufo Bromista siendo invisible en la aldea. Pero si Wislow se desprendio de la capa, seguro que tenia sus motivos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: No todos los dias se encuentra uno con una flor parlante. Y, en especial, con un personaje como Petaluma, una planta bulbosa algo arrogante con la que Pitufina se encuentra en el bosque. Por supuesto, Pitufina se muestra encantada y lleva a Petaluma con ella a la Aldea Pitufa... desencadenando un proceso que pondra en peligro a todos los Pitufos. Parece que las flores estan hechas para contemplarlas y no para escucharlas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo deja a los Pitufos reparando la presa del pueblo mientras el se va de excursion en busqueda de hierbas para sus pociones. Mientras esta fuera, Pitufo Filosofo provoca un revuelo al declarase a si mismo Rey y Papa Pitufo regresa a tiempo para evitar que la presa se destruya.

programme.title: La Novia De Escrupulo
programme.desc: Brenda, la pequena bruja, se siente rechazada: nadie la quiere llevar al Baile de las Escobas de este ano. Ay, si pudiera encontrar a algun chico guapo... Entonces conoce a Escrupuloso, el aprendiz del malvado mago Gargamel. Es muy apuesto, ¡y esta libre! Lo que ella no sabe es que Escrupuloso solamente esta interesado en su varita magica. Y lo que saben los Pitufos es que la van a ayudar a salir del aprieto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las pinturas del malvado Maestro son capaces de tele portar a sus modelos dentro del cuadro...para siempre! Papa pitufo le dice a Pintor que cambie las pinturas y en poco tiempo Maestro acaba dentro de uno de sus cuadros, al lado de su modelo de ensueno: Pitufina.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos se preparan para recuperar una concha marina que necesitan para liberar a un ermitano de las garras de la Bruja del Mar, la cual la maldijo con un aspecto horrible y un lenguaje dificil de entender. Los Pitufos consiguen recuperar la concha a tiempo para romper el maleficio y devolver al ermitano a su verdadero ser.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren una Fuente de la Juventud cuidada por un espantoso Troll que roba el libro magico de Papa Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo deja a los Pitufos reparando la presa del pueblo mientras el se va de excursion en busqueda de hierbas para sus pociones. Mientras esta fuera, Pitufo Filosofo provoca un revuelo al declarase a si mismo Rey y Papa Pitufo regresa a tiempo para evitar que la presa se destruya.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel esta decidido a sobrevolar la Aldea Pitufa para atrapar a un Pitufo y llevarlo a la Convencion de los Magos, e invoca a su libro de hechizos para que le ayude. Esto da lugar a una serie de divertidos contratiempos con su maquina voladora, y Gargamel vuelve a convertirse en el hazme reir de la Convencion de los Magos.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Pitufo Que Queria Ser Rey
programme.desc: Pitufo Sonador anhela convertirse en rey despues de leer una historia sobre reyes. Mientras esta en su barco, cae a traves de un remolino y llega a una tierra de pequenos seres que creen que Pitufo Sonador es su rey, desaparecido hace mucho tiempo. Cuando se enfrenta a los Norfnangs, los enemigos de esos pequenos seres, descubre que no son terrorificos en absoluto. Pitufo Sonador se da un golpe en la cabeza y descubre al despertar que todo habia sido un sueno, aunque encuentra en su gorro una joya identica a las que extraian esos pequenos seres de su mina.

programme.title: Pitufo En Rascacielos
programme.desc: Esta claro que una aldea de casas con forma de seta es bonita y alegre... Sin embargo, no resulta muy moderna a los ojos de Pitufo Arquitecto. Lo que los Pitufos necesitan es un rascacielos, un nuevo y atrevido concepto que cambiara su forma de vivir para siempre...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos descubren una Fuente de la Juventud cuidada por un espantoso Troll que roba el libro magico de Papa Pitufo.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel cree que crear a Pitufina fue el peor error de su vida. Pero, si pudiera lograr que recuperara su malignidad original, conseguiria a todos los Pitufos de un plumazo. ¿Volvera Pitufina a comportarse de forma malvada?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando los Pitufos llegan a la antigua China, descubren que el emperador nino corre peligro de ser depuesto. ¿Y por quien? ¡Por el malvado Garg-Fu-Yun, que quiere hacerse con el trono del nino!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado mago Gargamel ha conseguido unos huevos magicos de cristal citoplasmico que le permitiran intercambiar su cuerpo con el de Papa Pitufo. ¿Que otro plan mejor que ese podria haber? Una vez que este en el cuerpo de Papa Pitufo, llevara a todos los Pitufos hasta su caldero. Pero, por juegos del destino, Gargamel se transforma en Perro, el perro de los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Secreto Del Pantano De Las Sombras
programme.desc: Pitufo Grunon, que odia todo, detesta especialmente su propia fiesta de cumpleanos, por lo que decide esconderse en el Pantano de las Sombras. Alli encontrara extranos seres y vivira aventuras aun mas extranas mientras los demas Pitufos le buscan...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Posar para una escultura, sobre todo para una composicion enorme como la de Pitufo Pintor, es un trabajo agotador, y es imposible evitar moverse un poco. Ahora, Papa Pitufo ha encontrado la forma de que los modelos se queden completamente quietos. Sin embargo, tiene algunos inconvenientes, tal como los Pitufos comprobaran pronto...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Abuelo Pitufo nunca habia aparentado su edad, pero ahora esta mas joven que nunca tras haber entrado en contacto con el agua de la Fuente de la Juventud. Sasita tendra que cuidar de este nino milenario...

programme.title: Los Pitufos Y El Arbol Del Dinero
programme.desc: El mago malvado Gargamel ha elaborado otro plan diabolico con la ayuda de su madre, quien no es mas agradable que el. El quiere persuadir a los Pitufos con dinero pero ellos no saben lo que les espera. ¿Pitufo Goloso caera en la trampa?

programme.title: El Color Mas Pitufoso
programme.desc: Spectra es el hada de los colores, y con su rueda de los colores crea todos los azules, rojos, amarillos y verdes del mundo. Es amiga de Pitufo Pintor, pero, cuando este lleva a los Pitufitos a su morada en su ausencia, los Pitufitos se ponen a jugar con la rueda de los colores... y provocan que todos los colores desaparezcan de la Tierra. Y, lo que es aun peor: sin colores, el hada de los colores no puede vivir...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Goloso es un gran conocedor de la buena comida. Sin embargo, en la antigua Roma descubre un nuevo y delicioso plato y decide que quiere aprender la receta. Para ello, Pitufo Goloso primero debe ganar un concurso.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: En su busqueda de algo novedoso, Pitufo Vanidoso se pone un sombrero magico creado por Gargamel que le deja la cara hecha un adefesio. Mediante una argucia, Papa Pitufo consigue robarle el antidoto al malvado mago, logrando asi que Pitufo Vanidoso recupere su belleza.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Selwyn y Tallulah son un matrimonio de poderosos hechiceros. El problema es que estan todo el rato peleandose. La energia de sus discusiones esta formando una temible tormenta, y Papa Pitufo debe conseguir que hagan las paces antes de que la tormenta arrecie.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Debe ser por algo que ha comido. La gallina que ponia huevos pintados ahora pone huevos blancos corrientes. El escenario es la antigua Rusia, y el zar montara en colera si los Pitufos no encuentran una solucion.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Otra estupenda produccion del teatro de los Pitufos basada en los personajes de Alejandro Dumas. Incluye algunas lineas de Romeo y Julieta. Una obra maestra de la escena.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Esta vez, Gargamel tiene un plan infalible. Sin hacer caso de la risa burlona de Azrael, el malvado hechicero ha perfeccionado una sustancia magica a la que ha llamado «polvo temerario», que convertira a todos los Pitufos en temerarios e intrepidos aventureros. ¿Caera Papa Pitufo en la trampa de Gargamel? ¿Atrapara su enemigo a todos los Pitufos? ¿Tendra esta historia un final feliz?

programme.title: La Novia De Escrupulo
programme.desc: Brenda, la pequena bruja, se siente rechazada: nadie la quiere llevar al Baile de las Escobas de este ano. Ay, si pudiera encontrar a algun chico guapo... Entonces conoce a Escrupuloso, el aprendiz del malvado mago Gargamel. Es muy apuesto, ¡y esta libre! Lo que ella no sabe es que Escrupuloso solamente esta interesado en su varita magica. Y lo que saben los Pitufos es que la van a ayudar a salir del aprieto.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cuando una gota de la nueva pocion de Papa Pitufo cae en el libro de aventuras de los Pitufitos, el heroe de ficcion cobra vida. El intrepido Don Pitufo, que desea deshacer a los Pitufos del malvado Gargamel, lo captura con valentia...

programme.title: La Desgracia De Gargamel
programme.desc: Gargamel, el malvado e incompetente mago, intenta enganar a la gitana Esmeralda para que le de una formula para atrapar a los Pitufos. Por supuesto, la gitana demuestra ser mucho mas lista que Gargamel, y los Pitufos aun mas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: No todos los dias se encuentra uno con una flor parlante. Y, en especial, con un personaje como Petaluma, una planta bulbosa algo arrogante con la que Pitufina se encuentra en el bosque. Por supuesto, Pitufina se muestra encantada y lleva a Petaluma con ella a la Aldea Pitufa... desencadenando un proceso que pondra en peligro a todos los Pitufos. Parece que las flores estan hechas para contemplarlas y no para escucharlas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Te despiertas temprano por la manana, antes de que los demas Pitufos se hayan levantado de sus camas, para preparar sabrosos bizcochos de pitufrutas. Dedicas toda la manana a preparar pitufimanjares para el almuerzo. Despues, toda la tarde a tener la deliciosa cena lista a tiempo. ¿Y acaso los demas Pitufos te dan siquiera las gracias? Asi pues, Pitufo Goloso renuncia. La aldea esta en problemas... y pronto, tambien lo esta Pitufo Goloso.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: El malvado brujo Nemesis, antiguo enemigo de Abuelo Pitufo, acude en busca de el y de la Piedra de la Longevidad de los Pitufos. ¿Podra Abuelo Pitufo salvarse y proteger la piedra del poderoso hechicero?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos van al rescate de dos ninos y su abuelo, cuando un misterioso extranjero aparece haciendo que su trineo se rompa en pedazos. Al llamar a la puerta de Gargamel en busca de ayuda, no se dan cuenta de que estan poniendo en peligro sus vidas y la de los Pitufos...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada manana, los duendecillos del agua depositan rocio sobre las hojas del bosque. No imaginas todo lo que ocurrira cuando Pitufo Miedoso se transforme con la varita magica que crea las gotas de rocio...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una vez mas, el infalible plan de Gargamel para atrapar a los Pitufos ha fracasado. Los Pitufos aprovechan para gastarle una broma: disfrazados de pequenos angeles azules, le ensenaran a enmendar su conducta...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Salomon el adivino posee un amuleto que permite a su portador conocer el futuro. Se lo entrega amablemente (quiza demasiado amablemente) a Pitufo Poeta que, desde ese momento, podra saber que sucedera a continuacion...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Gargamel y Baltasar se ponen a los mandos de un Robotin gigante para obligar al rey Gerard a que les entregue a Pitufo Robotin. Cuando el Robotin esta a punto de destruir el castillo, Giganton, el nuevo, enorme y extrano amigo de Pitufo Robotin, vence al Robotin. Pitufo Robotin sufre danos durante la batalla, pero Pitufo Carpintero lo arregla y le implanta una caja de voz que le permite decir «¡Hola!».

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.sub-title: El Gran Sueno De Papa Pitufo
programme.desc: El sabio y prudente Papa Pitufo, sin el cual el pequeno pueblo azul estaria indefenso, sufre la mordedura del Monstruo del Sueno en el antiguo Japon. Cae dormido y, para despertarle, los Pitufos emprenden un viaje...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Poeta y Pintor se sienten poco valorados y huyen a una isla tormentosa sin saber que Gargamel los sigue hasta alli.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Por pura casualidad, un elefante que pasaba por el bosque se encuentra con Bebe Pitufo, y los Pitufos deciden crear un gran Circo. Van a visitar al hechicero infernal Baltazar y Bebe Pitufo se lo esta pasando genial...

programme.title: El Capricho De Travieso
programme.desc: ¿Sabias que, si atrapas un trol, este puede concederte un deseo? Resulta que Aloysius el trol ha quedado atrapado en una de las pitufitrampas de Gargamel. Pitufo Colerico le libera y, como recompensa, consigue que los demas Pitufos satisfagan todos sus caprichos. Esto acarrea un monton de problemas para los Pitufos, ya que los Pitufitos, en ocasiones, piden cosas que no son buenas para ellos... ni tampoco para los demas.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Una malvada hechicera lanza un hechizo a los Pitufos, obligandoles a amarse a si mismos en lugar de amar a los demas. Pitufo Vanidoso, que siempre ha actuado asi, estaba lejos en ese momento, pero nota el cambio a su regreso. Rompe el hechizo haciendo que todos los Pitufos coman un pastel de humildad cocinado por un mago.

programme.title: La Absopitufiasombrosa Maquina
programme.desc: Pitufo Genio inventa una maquina que hara que los Pitufos controlen el clima a su voluntad.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hoy se celebra la regata anual y todos los Pitufos han disenado sus propios botes, cada uno de los cuales refleja su personalidad. Sin embargo, Gargamel es capaz de predecir en que instante van a llegar los botes a este recodo del rio y ha preparado una desagradable sorpresa...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Los Pitufos hambrientos descubren una cueva en donde se encuentra oculta comida congelada custodiada por un trol tambien congelado quien fue encarcelado debido a su avaricia por un diamante magico. Mientras los Pitufos descongelan la cueva Gargamel roba la comida, pero el diamante magico lo transforma en una masa helada y el trol liberado ayuda gustosamente a los Pitufos a cargar la comida de regreso a su aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: La bruja Hogata promete a Gargamel un silbato magico si este le presenta al brujo de sus suenos. Sin embargo, ambos se enganan mutuamente con sus triquinuelas: Gargamel se disfraza de brujo, y el silbato magico de Hogata es simplemente un reclamo para aves.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Antes, en la Aldea Pitufa no habia reloj. Sin embargo, el tiempo se ha convertido de repente en algo precioso, y Pitufo Vanidoso elabora un plan para aprovecharse del nuevo reloj de la aldea. ¿Podran sobrevivir los Pitufos al ataque del tiempo?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Jamas debes comer dulces cuya procedencia desconozcas. Incluso si los dulces tienen forma de casa y estan en lo mas profundo de la Selva Negra. Los Pitufos no pueden resistirse a comer algunas partes de la casa de dulces y los problemas comienzan de inmediato.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Papa Pitufo se encuentra indefenso cuando se le acaban las bayas magicas que utiliza para sus pociones. Afortunadamente, los pequenos Pitufos encuentran un bebe de dragon en el bosque y con su ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Cada vez que Pitufo Perezoso se queda dormido, tiene la misma pesadilla una y otra vez: se encuentra en poder de Morfeo, un malvado hechicero que quiere capturar a tantas almas dormidas como sea posible. Uno tras otro, todos los Pitufos van cayendo en las garras de Morfeo. ¿Todos? Quiza no, si Papa Pitufo puede evitarlo. Para ello, Papa Pitufo acude al Arenero en busca de ayuda...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Hogatha se disfraza de premio de oro para observar a los Pitufos y capturarlos para sus ingredientes de belleza. Vanidoso acaba convenciendola de que pruebe su receta y acaba cubierta de barro de vuelta a casa de Gargamel.

programme.title: Secreto Del Pozo De La Aldea
programme.desc: ¿Por que Pitufo Torpe espera dia y noche junto al pozo de la aldea? ¿Cual es el deseo que quiere mantener en secreto? ¿Y como esta involucrado Gargamel en este asunto misterioso? ¿Lograra Gargamel atrapar por fin a los Pitufos?

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo no parece el mismo. Es educado, considerado, modesto y trata con cortesia a los demas Pitufos. A todos los Pitufos les preocupa que Pitufo Filosofo haya perdido todos los rasgos que conforman su personalidad. Y hacen bien en estar preocupados, ya que Filosofo ha sido victima de un artefacto denominado removedor de esencias que Escrupuloso, el aprendiz de Gargamel, esta utilizando... ¡Pero conseguiran recuperar la esencia de Filosofo!

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Pitufo Filosofo se siente preparado para la ocasion cuando empieza a preparar una receta de galletas. Esta convencido de que va a ganar el concurso, ya que ha tomado prestada una receta del libro de magia de Papa Pitufo. Sin embargo, una gran sorpresa y algunas situaciones desagradables aguardan al pobre Pitufo Filosofo y a toda la aldea.

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Las preocupaciones de Papa Pitufo hacen que le salgan verrugas. La unica forma de librarle de esta enfermedad causada por la indecision es que frote el cuerno de uno de los Verrugosos, los desalinados, viscosos, estupidos y brutales enemigos de las haditas del Bosque de los Sauces...

programme.title: Los Pitufos
programme.desc: Un extrano diablillo, que es todo un maestro de los juegos, desafia a los Pitufos en una competicion. Transforma a los Pitufitos en rigidas piezas de ajedrez y obliga a Pitufo Grunon, que nunca gana a ningun juego, a jugar para salvar las vidas de los Pitufitos. Pitufo Grunon va sintiendose mas seguro, realiza el movimiento correcto y consigue liberar a los Pitufos.

programme.title: GOLD CONNECTION - La Conexion del Oro
programme.desc: Cuatro amigos descubren un alijo de oro vietnamita de contrabando dejado por una organización criminal. Cuando el oro desaparece y se encuentra una barra con el dueño de una casa de empeño, los criminales no se detienen ante nada para recuperarlo y ver que los hombres que lo robaron sean tratados.

programme.title: 10 SHAOLIN DISCIPLES aka TEN SHAOLIN DISCIPLES - El Increible Shaolin
programme.desc: Eagle Han es enviado por la Corte Imperial para asesinar al Abad de Shaolin. Al completar su misión, Eagle se apodera de una escritura budista invaluable del Templo. Luego, una niña abandona el Templo en busca de recuperar las Escrituras. En su viaje conoce a otras nueve mujeres, todas las cuales han sido atacadas o salvajemente atacadas por seguidores de la Corte Manchú.

programme.title: FISTS of DRAGONS - Los pequeños grandes maestros
programme.desc: Dos astutos niños de kung fu se unen con un cazarrecompensas para llevar ante la justicia a un funcionario corrupto. ¡Grandes peleas acrobáticas al estilo Jackie Chan!

programme.title: KUNG FU EXECUTIONER - Los Asesinos del Kung Fu
programme.desc: Li, un artista marcial, vuelve a casa para descubrir que su padre está siendo acosado por un sindicato del crimen. Junto con un campeón de kung fu americano, jura vengarse cuando el sindicato mata a su padre.

programme.title: DRAGON, THE HERO,THE - El dragon heroe
